text:
Combined visualization (10%)
The problem: DJIA trades in the tens of thousands, gold in the thousands, and BTC swings from under $1,000 to over $60,000 across this period. Plot them raw on one chart and DJIA/BTC will flatten gold into an invisible line at the bottom — like putting an elephant, a dog, and a mouse on the same bathroom scale display.
The fix — indexing: we rescale every series so it starts at 100. Now we’re not asking “what’s the dollar price?” but “how much has this grown since Jan 2016?” — a fair comparison. We also use a log y-axis, since BTC’s growth is multiplicative (10x, 100x) rather than additive, and log scales make percentage moves visually comparable regardless of the starting size.

dj_long &lt;- monthly_dj |&gt;
  filter(date &gt;= as.Date(start_date)) |&gt;
  transmute(month = floor_date(date, "month"), close_value, asset = "DJIA")

btc_long &lt;- monthly_btc |&gt;
  transmute(month = floor_date(as.Date(date), "month"), close_value = adjusted, asset = "BTC")

gold_long &lt;- monthly_gold |&gt;
  transmute(month = floor_date(as.Date(date), "month"), close_value = adjusted, asset = "Gold")

combined &lt;- bind_rows(dj_long, btc_long, gold_long) |&gt;
  drop_na(close_value)

# keep only the date range where ALL THREE assets have data
range_by_asset &lt;- combined |&gt;
  group_by(asset) |&gt;
  summarize(min_month = min(month), max_month = max(month), .groups = "drop")

common_start &lt;- max(range_by_asset$min_month)
common_end &lt;- min(range_by_asset$max_month)

combined &lt;- combined |&gt;
  filter(month &gt;= common_start, month &lt;= common_end)

# index each series to 100 at the common start date
combined_indexed &lt;- combined |&gt;
  group_by(asset) |&gt;
  arrange(month) |&gt;
  mutate(index_100 = close_value / first(close_value) * 100) |&gt;
  ungroup()

ggplot(combined_indexed, aes(x = month, y = index_100, color = asset)) +
  geom_line(linewidth = 0.8) +
  scale_y_log10() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c(DJIA = "#1f78b4", BTC = "#e6550d", Gold = "#b15928")) +
  labs(
    title = "DJIA vs BTC vs Gold: Growth Since Jan 2016",
    subtitle = "Indexed to 100 at start, log scale so % moves are visually comparable",
    x = "Month", y = "Indexed Price (log scale, start = 100)", color = "Asset"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()
